We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The graph shows severe mitral stenosis, which is characterized by a high-pitched, holosystolic murmur that radiates to the axilla. Rumbling, delayed diastolic murmur heard best at the cardiac apex is characteristic of mitral stenosis with mitral regurgitation. Blowing, early diastolic murmur heard best at the Erb point is characteristic of aortic regurgitation. Harsh, late systolic murmur that radiates to the carotids is characteristic of mitral valve prolapse.
